growing dramatically in iowa montana missouri colorado and 
washington lt rodney burk of springfield mo described 
methamphetamine as kind of a poor mans cocaine that provides a 
longerlasting high and is readily available because it is made in 
america 
marijuana still the nations most widely used illicit drug 
despite the attention to paid to cocaine and crack is showing up 
in greater quantities in dallas and minneapolis police say 
and the psychedelic lsd so popular in the late 1960s is 
gaining popularity in such places as kansas city brockton mass 
and tacoma wash 
