<DOCNO> AP901008-0021 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the first world chess championship to be held in 
the united states in more than 80 years starts today with two 
highly different soviets competing in a battle of youthful daring 
against mature surgical precision 
the twomonth tourney of mental fireworks pits defending world 
champion garry kasparov against challenger and former champion 
anatoly karpov 
kasparov and karpov played their first match six years ago 
about 130 games later the two chess wizards remain arch rivals who 
command the board with expertise bordering on genius 
kasparov 27 the highestrated player in the history of chess 
is known for a gambling attacking style karpov 39 counters with 
methodical precise strategies 
kasparov is only two points ahead of his challenger and the 
difference in their temperaments looks politics and playing 
styles has heightened interest in the competition between the 
worlds two best chess players 
and its no secret that they dont get along 
when asked recently how they felt about each other kasparov 
replied do the yankees like the red sox 
kasparov is talkative flamboyant and fluent in english a 
media darling who tirelessly promotes chess fans in europe squeal 
at the mere sight of the darkhaired champion 
he has launched an anticommunist newspaper democratic russia 
in moscow and is the founder of a democratic political party 
during the match kasparov says he will play under the flag of 
the russian republic not the soviet union which he has said 
represents oppression and tyranny 
the fairhaired karpov is introverted and uses an interpreter 
but he has been known to interject english words at news 
conferences 
the older chessman a member of the communist party says he 
will play this match under the soviet flag he has been quoted as 
saying i have two loves communism and chess 
their chess styles match their temperaments kasparov gambles 
and goes for the jugular at the slightest hint of weakness from his 
opponent he doesnt worry about sacrificing pieces in the attack 
karpov plays with surgical precision resembling the style of a 
baseline tennis player he wins by making fewer mistakes 
kasparov wrested the world championship from karpov in 1985 
ending his 10year reign the younger man defended his title 
against karpov in 1986 in 1987 their championship match ended in 
a tie under the rules kasparov retained his title 
this years match will comprise 12 games in new york three 
times a week through nov 10 and 12 games in lyons france 
starting nov 24 
the 3 million championship is being staged in the theater of a 
midtown manhattan hotel it is the first world championship in the 
united states since 1907 
the winner will receive 17 million and the loser 13 million 
kasparov has said his earnings will fund my private interests 
and the political interest of the world karpov has said he will 
help victims of the chernobyl nuclear plant fire and promote chess 
in schools 
since world war ii seven of the world chess champions have come 
from the soviet union the only champion to break the soviet 
winning streak was american bobby fischer 
</TEXT>
