<TEXT>
alarmed by past terrorist attacks 
authorities have erected a sixfoothigh spiked wire fence in the 
seaside resort where britains governing conservatives opens their 
annual conference tuesday 
the threemilelong fence in the south coast town of bournemouth 
is the first of its kind ever put up to protect a political 
conference in britain 
it surrounds the bournemouth international center where the 
representatives meet and the highcliff hotel where leading party 
members are staying 
bournemouth officials said nearly 1500 police are on duty in an 
unprecedented security operation costing nearly 37 million 
independent television news reported that bournemouth councilors 
hope that someone will help the town pay the bill 
the fence is to protect the conservatives from the outlawed 
irish republican army which is fighting to end british rule in 
northern irerland 
during the conservatives 1984 party conference in brighton on 
the south coast an ira bomb blew up the hotel where prime minister 
margaret thatcher was staying she escaped but five other people 
were killed and 31 injured 
ian gow a conservative lawmaker and personal friend of mrs 
thatcher was murdered july 30 by the explosion of an ira bomb 
under his car 
on sept 27 a sound engineer found a lunch box packed with 
plastic explosive under a reading desk in a london club timed to 
go off half an hour after the start of a conference about 
terrorism the room had earlier been searched by police with dogs 
and given the all clear 
the ira claimed responsibility for that one too 
</TEXT>
