<TEXT>
speaking at a rally for marijuana 
legalization a kansas city mayoral candidate called for an end to 
the war on drugs 
if folks want to get high get drunk get stoned get peaceful 
or get fat lets let them said richard c tolbert after all 
isnt this still america 
the rally sunday at liberty memorial drew about of 500 people 
was part of the national hemp tour 90 staged to spread 
information on the possible benefits of legalization and commercial 
harvest of marijuana 
tolbert told the crowd society has learned to live in relative 
peace with one of the most harmful drugs of all alcohol 
why not regulate all of these drugs the same way we do alcohol 
and allow them to be sold in liquor stores he said yes of 
course we should keep them out of the hands of minor children we 
should not sell beer or crack cocaine in vending machines and we 
probably should not sell tobacco that way either 
whether your drug of choice is alcohol crack cocaine 
tobacco marijuana valium heroin chocolate designer drugs or my 
personal favorite sugar we should be willing to live and let 
live the former kansas city councilman said 
tolbert called the war on drugs a waste of time and said society 
instead should fight crimes where there is a suffering victim such 
as theft and rape 
