<TEXT>
a newly arrived kuwaiti refugee says 
resistance to iraqi forces virtually ended in his homeland after 
the occupiers began executing suspected resistance members 
sometimes in front of their families 
the former health ministry employee issa elnasrallah said the 
iraqis are forcing out kuwaitis to isolate the resistance 
his charges came as several hundred more kuwaiti refugees 
arrived sunday at the khafji border crossing in neighboring saudi 
arabia iraq had again relaxed restrictions on departing kuwaitis 
exiled kuwaiti officials say iraq is trying to chase away 
kuwaitis and repopulate the oilrich land with palestinians and 
iraqis 
nasrallah who fled with his wife and four children said many 
people in occupied kuwait believe iraq is preparing for combat 
there soon presumably expecting to do battle with the usled 
multinational force massed against it in saudi arabia 
they also want to isolate the resistance to have everyone but 
them leave theyre trying to force people out said nasrallah 
he said acts of resistance had stopped in kuwait city since the 
iraqis began killing anyone suspected of belonging to the 
resistance many in front of their families 
everybodys scared there they dont know when the iraqis will 
come in the house and kill them said yusuf alali 25 a kuwaiti 
airways pilot who also arrived during the weekend 
several hundred westerners are still believed to be hiding in 
kuwait fearful of being taken to iraq for use as human shields at 
military and other strategic installations 
iraq seized kuwait on aug 2 in a dispute over land and oil 
annexed the emirate and declared it an iraqi province 
later in august kuwaiti refugees reported that resistance 
fighters were staging desperate and daring attacks including 
suicide bombings at that time they said iraq had been unable to 
wipe them out 
exiled kuwaitis have directed the resistance from a forward 
command post in khafji three miles south of the border they had 
been smuggling in ammunition and communications equipment to help 
fighters inside kuwait 
in early september a senior guerrilla leader said the 
resistance had recruited thousands of volunteers from among kuwaiti 
refugees in saudi arabia at that time a senior saudi official 
said the resistance was growing in strength and stepping up attacks 
on the iraqi occupiers the latest opening of the border came 
friday after iraqi authorities intensified night searches in kuwait 
city refugees said the searches prompted many of them to leave 
out of fear 
iraqi troops were confiscating all identification papers in 
kuwait the refugees reported 
they said iraqi authorities had announced that everyone must 
hold identification cards issued in baghdad effectively making 
them all into iraqi citizens 
those arriving said iraqi troops at the border were seizing some 
men under age 40 and taking bribes to allow others to cross 
refugees claim young men are being sent back for iraqi military 
service 
the new opening of the border raised saudi fears the iraqis are 
planning attempts to infiltrate agents into the kingdom 
the new refugee influx is the largest since midseptember when 
7000 kuwaitis poured through over three days in the new crush 
more than 1000 refugees have arrived since friday 
an estimated 300000 kuwaiti refugees are in saudi arabia and 
neighboring persian gulf states before the invasion kuwait had a 
native population of about 600000 
</TEXT>
