the city and the police union 
blacks make up only 6 percent of the 1331member police force 
seventyseven percent of the officers are white the rest are 
hispanic or other minorities blacks account for 12 percent of the 
citys population 
city officials also were concerned by the high failure rate of 
blacks on the written physical and psychological portions of the 
july test of the 194 blacks who took the test 495 percent 
passed while 795 percent of the whites passed and 588 percent of 
the hispanics passed 
the city hired dr david morris president of the morris and 
mcdaniel consulting firm of washington dc to review the tests 
for any cultural biases 
morris said he found none but he did cite problems with the 
citys minority recruiting program 
in one instance recruiters pursued randm candidates at a 
shopping mall he said in another instance they recruited blacks 
who couldnt read and tried to teach them to read 
thats like sending a baseball coach or a football coach to a 
mall to recruit athletes just because theyre black morris 
