<TEXT>
jury selection began today in the assault 
trial of a man who is also a suspect in last months slayings of 
five college students in gainesville 
edward lewis humphrey who has been under intense scrutiny by 
investigators and the media since his arrest by brevard county 
authorities is accused of beating his 79yearold grandmother a 
charge both he and the grandmother deny 
retired judge theron a yawn visiting from alachua county to 
preside over the misdemeanor case summoned 20 prospective jurors 
for initial questioning the trial needs six jurors 
attorneys for humphrey say they expect it will take a long time 
to select a jury because of the publicity surrounding the unrelated 
slayings 
the 18yearold university of florida freshman was arrested on 
the assault charge aug 29 shortly afterward investigators 
publicly named him as a suspect in the deaths of the five students 
whose bodies were discovered the three preceding days 
humphrey has remained jailed on 1 million bond if convicted 
he could be sentenced to up to 5 years in prison 
humphrey is charged in connection with an incident the night of 
aug 29 when he left gainesville and returned to his indiatlantic 
home police were called and his grandmother elna hlavaty told 
them humphrey had hit her 
she has since refused to press charges and has denied that her 
grandson hit her 
