surveillance cameras at 16 locations the system infuriates airin 
residents who say the close surveillance invades their privacy 
people in this town are extremely sensitive about their 
privacy because most of them have hidden pasts that they do not 
want to be revealed said a coffee shop owner who spoke on 
condition of anonymity 
do you know the feeling when you are consistently watched 
arimura asked here police seem to assume that everyone is a 
potential criminal what can be more discouraging 
laborers also complain that police do not investigate complaints 
that gangsters are taking advantage of the workers 
its as if we are lower than gangsters one laborer said 
when i heard about the bribery case i felt like shouting that it 
was our money the cop was getting from gangs and he was helping 
those gangs exploit us 
said another middleaged worker we are outcasts of society 
who got kicked out of the ordinary world and ended up here we are 
being sandwiched between police and gangsters but where else can 
we go now 
