western michigan university has received 
a 5 million grant from the us department of education to 
establish a national center to improve evaluation methods for 
educators officials announced monday 
the grant the largest in the universitys history will 
establish the center for research on educational accountability on 
nov 1 within the universitys existing evaluation center 
the center will become the focal point for efforts to improve 
measurement procedures for evaluating the performance of teachers 
and administrators in both public and private schools 
personnel evaluation has always been something of a hot 
potato said daniel l stufflebeam who will serve as the 
centers director 
public demand for accountability has pushed many districts and 
even entire states to adopt misguided teacher evaluation methods 
he said a goal of the center will be to provide schools with 
evaluation models that are unbiased and efficient 
western was selected for the grant after a sixmonth nationwide 
competition the center 1 million in federal funds annually for 
five years 
