legs etched in mud 
the photographs showed the huge crater on sherwood crescent at 
the edge of the main a74 highway from england to scotland the 
fuelladen wing section exploded there damaging or destroying 20 
houses and vaporizing some victims 
there were also photos of parts of the plane of debris hanging 
in trees and lines of searchers looking for victims 
boyd read large sections of his report on the police emergency 
response into the record and was questioned by fraser 
the inquiry expected to last three months is focusing on the 
causes of death and ways to prevent a similar disaster not on 
criminal responsibility 
boyd said scottish police investigators went to helsinki 
finland in january 1989 to investigate a warning telephoned to the 
us embassy there dec 5 that a bomb would be carried on a pan 
american world airways flight from frankfurt in the following two 
weeks 
there was no evidence to connect the helsinki warning with the 
lockerbie incident he said 
under crossexamination boyd said the warning mentioned a 
particular person who was investigated and said he still believed 
no connection existed 
he agreed that other unspecified warnings were made to 
embassies in helsinki in 1988 in what appeared to be a personal 
vendetta against a named individual 
new york attorney stephen pounian representing the families of 
american victims tried to ask boyd if police had information on a 
warning to pan am about a toshiba radio 
fraser leaped to his feet and protested saying that went to 
the core of the criminal investigation 
