market is much much more difficult than it was two three or four 
years ago 
he cited the decline of the junk bond market which financed a 
number of takeovers in the 1980s 
he also noted that gannett has a shareholder rights offering 
plan that would kick in after somebody acquires 15 percent of the 
stock the plan would make it prohibitively expensive for a suitor 
to acquire more shares mccorkindale said 
