<TEXT>
whether he wants to or not tony goldwyn seems 
destined to become a movie star 
hes got the looks dark blond curly hair iceblue eyes and a 
slightly offcenter smile 
hes got the luck playing the yuppie wall street villain in 
ghost the surprise movie hit of the summer a romantic fantasy 
that bested beatty swamped schwarzenegger and even wiped out 
willis 
hes got the training nearly a decade of stage and television 
work including studying two years at the london academy of music 
and dramatic art and playing half dozen summers at the williamstown 
festival in massachusetts 
hes got the pedigree descended from a famous hollywood family 
the 30yearold goldwyn also has a levelheaded sense of self in 
a business where sudden success unreality and hyperbole rule the 
day 
i realize acting is a profession and i want to be in it for 
the rest of my life he says a lot of the roles i was offered 
after ghost were onedimensional bad guys i thought it was 
better to make noise quietly and do something i believe in 
consider his latest project despite his current big hollywood 
flick goldwyn is toiling these days for minimum wages in a small 
offbroadway theater in greenwich village hes costarring with 
richard venture in the sum of us a comedy by australian 
playwright david stevens author of breaker morant 
its a beautiful play which i first did at williamstown 
goldwyn says 
set in a bluecollar suburb of melbourne the sum of us 
concerns the complex relationship between a son who is gay and a 
father who accepts him for what he is 
what i think is most interesting about the play is that david 
stevens examines a relationship that is completely unconditional 
and nonjudgmental and the problems that that can create he 
says 
goldwyn began his career while at brandeis university on 
stage it was a conscious effort to distance himself from an 
impeccable showbusiness pedigree that he says could close as many 
doors as it could open 
one grandfather was movie mogul samuel goldwyn the man behind 
such classics as the best years of our lives and wuthering 
heights the other was broadway playwright sidney howard author 
of they knew what they wanted and the silver cord 
mom is onetime stage actress jennifer howard dad is samuel 
goldwyn jr a force in todays hollywood as producer of such 
recent film hits as mystic pizza 
their son takes his familys celluloid celebrity in stride 
they in turn protected him from it 
i felt naive when i finally got into show business goldwyn 
says i felt i didnt know anything about the movies because i 
had been so sheltered from it as a kid 
i was very close to my grandparents and parents but they were 
so sensitive to the negative aspects of the hollywood world that 
they kept us completely separated from it i was never involved in 
my fathers work 
there never were movie stars around kids in school used to 
ask me what movie stars do you know and i was embarrassed 
because i didnt know any 
goldwyns decision to become an actor was greeted with mixed 
feelings by his parents 
my mothers whole family was from the theater and she had been 
an actress in new york as a younger woman goldwyn recalls so 
the theater held great romance for her she thought it was great 
my father was terrified but he said do what you want to 
do goldwyn says but he was nervous about it 
father and son have not worked together at least not yet 
our relationship is primarily personal and i wouldnt want to 
threaten it by getting into business together goldwyn says we 
have such a good solid relationship as a father and a son that its 
not worth it to either of us to muck it up 
goldwyn found out about the role in ghost through his wife 
jane musky who was production designer on the film but director 
jerry zucker thought he was too nice and sympathetic to play 
the man who tries to come between patrick swayze and demi moore 
only after the producer and the scriptwriter saw an audition 
tape goldwyn made and raved about his performance did zucker 
consider him for the job 
goldwyn and his wife live with their new daughter anna in 
hoboken nj 
i have avoided the whole hollywood scene largely because it 
doesnt appeal to me he says when i first went back to 
california to work in television it was rough i didnt know 
anybody and yet people thought i did so that made it even harder 
id walk into an office and they would say oh i know your 
dad so their perspective is oh this is just another kid from a 
showbusiness family who thinks he wants to be an actor i dont 
want that to be the focus of things 
ghost has changed that after he finishes his run in the 
sum of us goldwyn will portray jody powell president jimmy 
carters press secretary in a television movie for ted turner 
about the iran hostage crisis 
the bottom line is that its a struggle for anyone to be an 
actor he says now that ghost has become a success the 
family connection has taken on a whole new meaning people think it 
is wonderful and say gee isnt it amazing that youve made your 
mark and now another goldwyn does his own thing and that has 
been great 
