whats americas best unknown rock band heres a vote for new 
york citys finest the del lords 
the del lords music little tales of life and redemption with 
three guitars and drums seems almost quaint today but its done 
with intelligence and dedication all the more impressive since 
theyve never achieved the stardom some predicted for them six 
years ago 
this is a quartet of workingclass new yorkers who havent lost 
their pride in the city despite anger at whats become of it 
somewhere in queens scott kempner sings the sun is always 
shining 
but enough sociology lovers who wander is a collection that 
illuminates common life from a landlord who sues a tenant for 
being a day late and a dollar short to of course lovers who 
wander the del lords never quite give in to their frustrations 
and one suspects its largely due to the healing powers of music 
most of kempners songs depict various stages of relationships 
from the anticipation of i need love to the resignation of 
learn to let go while the del lords retain their musical 
toughness the material here demands more subtlety than the band 
has shown in the past and they handle it with aplomb 
the only wish here is that kempner loosen the reins on his band 
only twice does he let someone else write the songs and one of 
them rockabye written and sung by drummer frank funaro is 
terrific guitarist eric ambels voice enough to carry a strong 
solo album a year ago isnt heard until the final song kempner 
wrings as much emotion from his gruff bronxaccented voice as can 
be expected but hed be better off spreading the vocals around 
more 
much of rock n roll is fantasybased but the del lords have 
both feet firmly on the ground and their victories are also their 
listeners call it music you can use 
by david bauder associated press writer 
