<TEXT>
geoffrey moore is a referee whos not looking 
forward to his next call he could blow the whistle on the longest 
economic expansion in us peacetime history 
moore and six colleagues affiliated with the national bureau of 
economic research in cambridge mass will decide perhaps before 
years end on whether the latest recession has begun 
many private economists believe a downturn is imminent if it 
is not already here and moore said he expects his committee to 
decide before december whether the next downturn is under way 
the current growth cycle which would be eight years old in 
november already has broken the previous peacetime record of 58 
months from march 1975 to january 1980 the alltime record of 106 
months of economic growth ran from february 1961 to december 1969 
a time period that included the vietnam war 
the last recession lasted from july 1981 to november 1982 
according to moore and his colleagues on the bureaus business 
cycle dating committee the next would be the eighth that moore has 
been involved in defining 
i dont look forward to recessions he says i just try to 
identify them after theyve started 
the bureau a private research organization of several hundred 
academic economists scattered around the world has become 
recognized as the arbiter of business cycles founded in 1920 it 
is funded by corporate contributions and government and foundation 
grants 
its tables showing the extent of business growth and contraction 
since 1854 have been published regularly in commerce department 
publications beginning in 1961 
thats what has made it official more than anything else 
that a government agency would use its data moore said in a 
recent interview 
he retired from the bureau staff in 1979 after 40 years to 
become director of the center for international business cycle 
research at columbia university a position he still holds at age 
76 however he still is affiliated with nber 
their calls are widely accepted said adren cooper a 
commerce department spokesman since the nber has been doing that 
theres been no controversy that i know of 
the government itself does not announce the beginning and end of 
business cycles out of fear that it would be accused of making 
politically manipulated decisions 
the nber definition of a recession is more complicated than the 
oftenused formula of two consecutive quarterly declines in the 
gross national product the broadest measure of the nations 
economic activity that was coined by arthur okun chairman of 
president lyndon johnsons council of economic advisers 
the nbers broader definition is a recurring period of decline 
in total output income employment and trade usually lasting from 
six months to a year and marked by widespread contractions in many 
sectors of the economy bureau spokeswoman donna zeritz said 
federal reserve chairman alan greenspan also uses a more complex 
definition of a recession 
a recession is a cumulative process of deterioration in which 
events feed on each other causing a major economic decline he 
told congress last month a process in which the economy is 
deteriorating in a cumulative interactive manner is a true 
recession 
although greenspan and the bush administration contend the 
economy is not now in a downturn many private economists disagree 
saying the economy began contracting during the current quarter 
others say a recession is likely before years end 
moore describes the criteria for measuring a recession as the 
3d words duration depth and defusion 
as for duration the longest recession lasted 65 months from 
october 1873 to march 1879 the shortest lasted six months from 
january to july 1980 the great depression went on for 43 months 
starting in august 1929 and ending in march 1933 
in addition to duration moore said we look at measures of 
aggregate economic activity such as nonfarm employment industrial 
production real gnp real income and real sales 
we get a variety of measures of that sort and see whether the 
decline thats begun is comparable with the magnitude of previous 
cycles he explained 
defusion moore said means the decline is experienced widely 
and not contained in just one or two industries such as housing and 
automobiles 
joining moore in deciding the peaks and troughs of business 
cycles are martin feldstein of harvard university the nber 
president who became economic adviser to president reagan as the 
nation was emerging from the last recession robert hall the 
committee chairman from stanford university william branson of 
princeton university benjamin friedman of harvard victor 
zarnowitz of the university of chicago business school and robert 
gordon of northwestern university 
the bureau also is credited with developing the commerce 
departments index of leading economic indicators designed to 
forecast economic activity six months to nine months in advance 
</TEXT>
