<TEXT>
a new european proposal to slash government 
farm subsidies to break a deadlock with the united states in world 
trade talks would sacrifice farmers an organization of european 
farm groups said monday 
european agriculture ministers considered the plan monday for 
the first time since it was unveiled last week by the european 
commission the executive body of the 12nation european 
community 
the ministers planned to discuss the proposal next monday after 
getting more details on how the plan would affect farmers 
copa an umbrella organization for farm groups announced its 
opposition to the plan immediately copa president joseph yverneau 
said the proposals are unacceptable and we totally reject them 
they are totally sacrificing the agriculture sector he told 
a news conference we should not be put on our knees 
yverneau a french farmer estimated that at least half the 
farmers in europe would be affected adversely by the farm plan 
the communitys new proposal calls for a 30 percent reduction in 
farm subsidies for such major products as cereals rice sugar and 
livestock over the period 1986 to 1996 a 10 percent cut is offered 
in fruits vegetables and tobacco 
no specific trims are suggested in the communitys costly export 
subsidy program but the proposal signals a willingness to 
negotiate reductions with other nations 
germanys agriculture minister ignaz kiechle said the proposal 
didnt gain much initial support from the european farm officals 
he said 10 of the 12 farm chiefs were critical to very critical 
of the proposal 
british agriculture secretary john gummer who supports subsidy 
trims challenged the united states to meet the trading blocs 
proposal 
i would very much like to see the americans match it he 
said 
the dispute over farm payments has stalled the uruguay round of 
international trade talks which are designed to overhaul the world 
trading system 
the fouryear negotiations which end in december are aimed at 
reducing barriers to trade in 15 areas including agriculture 
textiles and other manufactured goods and services such as banking 
and investment 
the american push to get the community to do more to cut its 
farm payments has angered its trading partner 
gummer said the export subsidies are part and parcel of the 
communitys farm program 
just because the united states doesnt like the system we use 
doesnt mean for some reason or other we shouldnt have a 
measurement which is fair to everybody he said 
he also told reporters the us government is a very major 
subsidizer of its farmers 
the bush administration is expected to unveil a new bargaining 
position on farm payments before a deadline next monday at the 
trade talks 
the us position is expected to include a 10year plan for 
reductions of up to 70 percent in domestic supports and import 
duties and more than that in export subsidies 
the us has backed off a previous demand for elimination of 
export subsidies 
the american plan also would force the community to widen its 
markets to foreign farm goods and slash farm payments that 
encourage overproduction 
the trade ministers gather later this week to discuss the 
proposal before it is formally put on the table at the trade talks 
the uruguay round is being held under the auspices of the 
general agreement on tariffs and trade a forum and agreement for 
removing trade barriers 
</TEXT>
