<TEXT>
trading on a soviet stock exchange could start 
next year but foreigners probably will remain on the sidelines 
until the ruble is convertible the chairman of the new york stock 
exchange said monday 
its not going to look like some kind of enormous exchange 
but it could begin in a modest way chairman john phelan jr said 
in an interview at moscows international trade center i think 
its a real possibility 
phelan and a delegation of 20 prominent wall street businessmen 
were invited to moscow to give a threeday seminar on the nuts and 
bolts of running a stock market dealings in stocks and bonds has 
been illegal in the soviet union since the 1917 revolution 
the kremlin with the enthusiastic backing of budding soviet 
speculators and entrepreneurs is preparing to allow the return of 
financial markets as part of the transition to a free market 
economy the most radical economic blueprints under consideration 
call for the establishment of a stock exchange within 100 days 
phelan predicted that whatever economic plan is finally adopted 
within the next 18 months the government will have reorganized 
financial structures permitted the development of private 
companies and lifted legal restrictions on private transactions 
between individuals 
that would be the logical time for the stock exchange to 
form he said adding it could begin as soon as late 1991 
more than 400 soviet bankers economists academics and 
government officials attended the crash course on securities 
american style seeking explanations for several concepts foreign 
to communist ideology and to their command economy 
how does a company get listed on the nyse one asked how do you 
prevent the government from meddling in market prices do american 
stock exchanges compete with one another how are dividends paid 
joseph grano president for retail sales and marketing of 
painewebber inc said it was critical that private ownership 
develop at the same time as a stock exchange for this dream to 
come to fruition 
he recommended the privatization of large state enterprises 
particularly in the oil industry before allowing more private 
ownership of smaller riskier businesses 
they need some success stories and if they can show a high 
concentration of workers a high concentration of investors how it 
works and how successful it can be then i believe youve started 
changes in the mindset grano said in an interview 
since june the government has permitted the creation of 
jointstock companies although it usually retains a majority of 
shares finance minister valentin pavlov told the seminar more than 
400 such companies have been set up 
the genies out of the bottle nothing can get it back in 
again said william schreyer chairman and chief executive 
officer of merrill lynch amp co inc during a break in the seminar 
phelan later told a news conference that longterm foreign 
investment in a soviet stock market probably would require a fully 
convertible ruble the right to export profits and the right to 
receive dividends in a stable currency the state now controls the 
price of the ruble against world currencies 
the soviet public will need to overcome its lingering sentiment 
that profits are wrong and based on exploitation and its fear of 
taking financial risks several wall street participants said 
you have to learn to fall before you can walk said lawyer 
joseph flon there will be ups and there will be downs the 
market reflects changes in society changes in the world 
schreyer said public education is still needed but added i 
just got the sense that maybe profit wasnt quite as dirty a word 
as it was 
the soviet government has licensed one brokerage house although 
it hasnt started work yet a committee of business people said it 
hopes to register the first stock exchange in moscow next month 
regardless of whether the government has passed the necessary laws 
we dont have anything we dont have space we dont have the 
specialists said banker yuri chetverikov we have only ideas 
and people are very eager to structure this kind of business 
</TEXT>
