soybean futures prices soared as much as 17 cents a bushel 
monday on the chicago board of trade amid heavy speculative buying 
spurred by harvest delays in the soggy midwest grain futures also 
advanced 
on other commodity markets energy futures rose precious metals 
were mixed pork futures fell sharply and cattle were mixed 
