services inc in bloomington ill 
cold rainy weather kept farmers from their fields across a 
broad band of the midwestern soybean country sunday and monday 
farmers in some areas may have to wait two or three days for fields 
to dry out said gerald zusel manager of balfour maclaine corps 
graintrading operations in chicago 
in addition to delaying the soybean harvest which is less than 
half complete rain can cause yield losses 
every time you wet a mature soybean pod and it dries out 
again it cracks open a little more and the beans can fall out so 
more of them end up on the ground and fewer of them end up in the 
machine armstrong said 
