with what the company expected because of the soft state of the 
nations economy 
in last years second quarter interco reported a profit of 
1186 million or 243 per share but that included the sale of 
several companies including ethan allen furniture and senack 
shoes which brought the company 210 million 
sales from continuing operations in the quarter ended aug 31 
were 369 million down 14 percent from 430 million in the same 
period a year ago sales from the companys core businesses in last 
years third quarter were 3713 million 
in july interco reached an agreement with its numerous 
creditors on a complicated deal to restructure more than 16 
billion in debt that the company took on in 1988 to fend off a 
hostile takeover attempt 
the deal between interco and its banks mediumterm noteholders 
and subordinated debenture holders helped the company avert 
bankruptcy 
since 1988 interco has been selling off subsidiaries in an 
attempt to repay its debts it has retained four companies 
converse inc florsheim shoes lane co and broyhill furniture 
industries 
